00:12:14,100 --> 00:12:15,133
Thank you.

261
00:12:16,000 --> 00:12:17,500
But are you really happy?

262
00:12:17,500 --> 00:12:18,700
That we won?

263
00:12:19,200 --> 00:12:20,300
Of course.

264
00:12:20,933 --> 00:12:23,000
I just hoped
I didn't fall asleep.

265
00:12:23,800 --> 00:12:25,300
[NYX] Speaking of that...

266
00:12:25,833 --> 00:12:29,933
Isobel's got something to say.

267
00:12:29,933 --> 00:12:30,800
Hmm.

268
00:12:30,800 --> 00:12:33,000
- I have nothing to say.
- Hey. Pst!

269
00:12:33,000 --> 00:12:34,233
Girl, just admit it.

270
00:12:34,867 --> 00:12:35,933
Come on...

271
00:12:35,933 --> 00:12:38,400
You guys are enjoying this
and I don't like it.

272
00:12:38,400 --> 00:12:39,367
[NYX] Hmm!

273
00:12:39,367 --> 00:12:41,067
Come on, Isobel.

274
00:12:41,433 --> 00:12:42,967
- We believe in you.
- [ISOBEL SCOFFS]

275
00:12:42,967 --> 00:12:44,000
[NYX] Yeah...

276
00:12:44,000 --> 00:12:45,867
Don't you know
how to say sorry?

277
00:12:45,867 --> 00:12:48,000
- I do, Dessalyn.
- [DAPHNE] Then say it!

278
00:12:49,833 --> 00:12:51,000
- [RETCHES]
- [NYX] Oh...

279
00:12:51,900 --> 00:12:52,900
[BREATH QUIVERS]

280
00:12:53,500 --> 00:12:54,667
I'm...

281
00:12:54,667 --> 00:12:56,000
- [NYX] What was that?
- [ISOBEL] Sorr...

282
00:12:56,000 --> 00:12:56,967
Huh?

283
00:12:56,967 --> 00:12:58,000
S-So...

284
00:12:58,467 --> 00:12:59,533
- What?
- What was that?

285
00:12:59,533 --> 00:13:01,000
[ISOBEL SIGHS] I'm so...

286
00:13:01,533 --> 00:13:04,500
[SIGHS] I'm so...rry.

287
00:13:04,500 --> 00:13:05,467
- Oh.
- Zero energy?

288
00:13:05,467 --> 00:13:06,900
- What?
- One more!

289
00:13:06,900 --> 00:13:08,433
[ISOBEL BREATHES DEEPLY]

290
00:13:08,433 --> 00:13:10,000
I'm sorry!

291
00:13:10,000 --> 00:13:12,000
Why does your apology
feel like a threat?

292
00:13:12,000 --> 00:13:13,500
- Nonchalant.
- Exactly.

293
00:13:13,500 --> 00:13:15,800
Why don't you try
to be more sincere?

294
00:13:15,800 --> 00:13:17,033
Try harder.

295
00:13:18,400 --> 00:13:19,833
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

296
00:13:19,833 --> 00:13:20,900
I'm sorry.

297
00:13:22,500 --> 00:13:24,900
It's okay,
I accept your apology.

298
00:13:24,900 --> 00:13:25,967
[MARLA] But, guys...

299
00:13:26,500 --> 00:13:28,400
Migo was a total loser.

300
00:13:28,400 --> 00:13:29,533
[DAPHNE] I know, right?!

301
00:13:29,533 --> 00:13:31,200
- He'll get kicked out.
- Right!

302
00:13:31,200 --> 00:13:33,000
- That's so right! For sure!
- I'm so excited!

303
00:13:33,000 --> 00:13:34,200
[PHONE CHIMES]

304
00:13:34,200 --> 00:13:37,033
They just posted our long test
results from Mr. Ramirez.

305
00:13:43,967 --> 00:13:45,200
- Huh?!
- [GASPS]

306
00:13:45,200 --> 00:13:46,267
What?

307
00:13:46,267 --> 00:13:47,367
- [GASPS]
- [NYX] What?!

308
00:13:47,967 --> 00:13:49,133
[DAPHNE] What the hell!

309
00:13:49,133 --> 00:13:50,767
How?! Migo...

310
00:13:51,967 --> 00:13:52,933
Passed?!

311
00:13:52,933 --> 00:13:54,033
This is anomalous!

312
00:13:54,033 --> 00:13:55,067
Anomalous?!

313
00:13:55,100 --> 00:13:58,067
- Oh my god, how did he pass?
- Crazy as heck!

314
00:13:58,067 --> 00:14:01,000
Why did Mr. Ramirez give Migo
such a high grade?

315
00:14:01,333 --> 00:14:03,200
- I know, right?
- He doesn't deserve it!

316
00:14:04,333 --> 00:14:07,967
But do you, guys,
actually think...

317
00:14:07,967 --> 00:14:10,300
that Migo's connected
with Mr. Ramirez?

318
00:14:12,933 --> 00:14:14,933
I never saw it in that angle.

319
00:14:15,900 --> 00:14:19,433
Perhaps we should look more
into Mr. Ramirez's background.

320
00:14:19,433 --> 00:14:21,200
[APRIL] It's probably just
a fluke.

321
00:14:21,467 --> 00:14:24,333
Maybe, Mr. Ramirez has nothing
to do with Migo.

322
00:14:24,900 --> 00:14:26,233
So, let's put a pin on that.

323
00:14:27,033 --> 00:14:28,067
[MARLA] No!

324
00:14:28,433 --> 00:14:30,067
I think Isobel is right.

325
00:14:30,867 --> 00:14:33,067
Mr. Ramirez should be
our next target.

326
00:14:33,600 --> 00:14:34,833
It's not right

327
00:14:34,833 --> 00:14:36,967
that we're keeping a teacher
who's an enabler,

328
00:14:36,967 --> 00:14:38,433
and then he just keeps
getting in our way.

329
00:14:38,433 --> 00:14:39,867
What is going on?

330
00:14:40,867 --> 00:14:42,500
Why are we on the same page?

331
00:14:42,500 --> 00:14:44,967
[NYX] Wow! Shh! Shh!

332
00:14:45,967 --> 00:14:46,967
Oh?!

333
00:14:46,967 --> 00:14:48,467
What's with you?

334
00:14:48,467 --> 00:14:49,433
Ha!

335
00:14:50,033 --> 00:14:51,267
I think...

336
00:14:51,267 --> 00:14:52,500
[ISOBEL] Is something itching?

337
00:14:53,267 --> 00:14:56,033
I think there's a 40% chance...

338
00:14:56,033 --> 00:14:58,167
that Mr. Ramirez helped Migo.

339
00:14:58,600 --> 00:15:00,200
He is a man after all.

340
00:15:01,000 --> 00:15:03,033
Men only protect other men.

341
00:15:03,033 --> 00:15:05,200
Don't go down this rabbit hole.

342
00:15:05,633 --> 00:15:09,033
If Mr. Ramirez finds out that
we're investigating him,

343
00:15:09,033 --> 00:15:11,067
we'll face the principal again.

344
00:15:11,067 --> 00:15:12,600
We'll trigger Principal Mckenna.

345
00:15:12,600 --> 00:15:15,067
[NYX] Ah! Principal's Office?

346
00:15:15,067 --> 00:15:16,300
I agree with her.

347
00:15:16,933 --> 00:15:18,133
Let's not do this, please.

348
00:15:18,533 --> 00:15:22,600
I think we should focus
with the boys.

349
00:15:22,600 --> 00:15:24,133
With a capital Z.

350
00:15:24,433 --> 00:15:27,000
Mr. Ramirez looks harmless
anyway.

351
00:15:27,000 --> 00:15:28,467
Yeah, and I'm sure

352
00:15:28,467 --> 00:15:31,500
Migo just hacked the system
to alter his grades.

353
00:15:31,500 --> 00:15:34,000
I don't think Mr. Ramirez
would even...

354
00:15:34,000 --> 00:15:35,467
help Migo,

355
00:15:35,500 --> 00:15:38,233
or risk his reputation
for someone like him.

356
00:15:39,933 --> 00:15:42,667
He's one of the best teachers
in SOSH.

357
00:15:44,967 --> 00:15:46,000
Okay.

358
00:15:47,133 --> 00:15:49,033
But I just have to ask, April...

359
00:15:50,467 --> 00:15:53,367
Why are you defending
Mr. Ramirez?

360
00:15:53,367 --> 00:15:54,433
Woah!

361
00:15:55,600 --> 00:15:57,933
[APRIL] I'm not defending him,
Marla.

362
00:15:57,933 --> 00:16:00,033
All I'm saying is
we need to get a grip.

363
00:16:00,400 --> 00:16:02,500
You're all becoming obsessed
with revenge.

364
00:16:02,500 --> 00:16:03,933
You're getting too emotional.

365
00:16:03,933 --> 00:16:05,400
You're imagining things.

366
00:16:05,933 --> 00:16:07,100
I'm saying...

367
00:16:07,100 --> 00:16:08,567
let's reorient to the data.

368
00:16:08,600 --> 00:16:09,733
[DAPHNE SCOFFS]

369
00:16:09,733 --> 00:16:11,033
You want data?

370
00:16:11,333 --> 00:16:13,600
Well, here's some data for you.

371
00:16:14,567 --> 00:16:16,300
Did you know

372
00:16:16,300 --> 00:16:19,300
that Mr. Ramirez is getting
cozy with students?

373
00:16:19,300 --> 00:16:20,333
- It's true!
- [APRIL] Was it with you?

374
00:16:20,333 --> 00:16:22,167
Yes--
I mean, not with me!

375
00:16:22,600 --> 00:16:25,367
He's fooling around even if
he's got a fiancée.

376
00:16:25,733 --> 00:16:27,300
[NYX] No way!

377
00:16:27,300 --> 00:16:34,233
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

378
00:16:36,300 --> 00:16:38,100
[DOOR CREAKS SHUT]

379
00:16:44,567 --> 00:16:46,600
[NYX] You swear
on Beyoncé's life?

380
00:16:46,600 --> 00:16:47,633
Yes, girl!

381
00:16:47,633 --> 00:16:49,200
I swear on Beyoncé's life!

382
00:16:49,200 --> 00:16:50,700
- That serious?
- I swear!

383
00:16:50,700 --> 00:16:52,000
Why? You think I'm delusional?

384
00:16:52,000 --> 00:16:52,933
Yeah.

385
00:16:52,933 --> 00:16:54,600
- [DAPHNE] No, as if!
- An itchy one.

386
00:16:54,600 --> 00:16:57,133
[DAPHNE] I got this straight
from Scarlet.

387
00:16:57,133 --> 00:17:01,467
Mr. Ramirez ghosted her
after months of fooling around.

388
00:17:01,467 --> 00:17:03,467
But, why didn't you report it?

389
00:17:03,467 --> 00:17:06,600
Actually,
I was already going to, but...

390
00:17:06,600 --> 00:17:08,500
Scarlet filed
a leave of absence,

391
00:17:08,500 --> 00:17:10,333
and eventually, she dropped out.

392
00:17:10,333 --> 00:17:12,333
Besides, I don't have
enough evidence.

393
00:17:12,733 --> 00:17:16,233
I thought, is it worth risking
my scholarship?

394
00:17:16,267 --> 00:17:17,467
That's it.

395
00:17:17,467 --> 00:17:18,533
That's not data.

396
00:17:19,067 --> 00:17:20,267
That's gossip.

397
00:17:20,267 --> 00:17:22,333
Besides, Scarlet is
your main source?

398
00:17:22,767 --> 00:17:24,033
Does she not use...

399
00:17:24,733 --> 00:17:26,067
...ChatGPT?

400
00:17:26,067 --> 00:17:27,333
- Oh my!
- Eww!

401
00:17:27,333 --> 00:17:29,400
Who uses ChatGPT?

402
00:17:31,433 --> 00:17:34,333
If we're able
to get a proof of that,

403
00:17:35,233 --> 00:17:37,200
we can have Mr. Ramirez fired.

404
00:17:37,200 --> 00:17:39,433
And even better,
get Migo kicked out!

405
00:17:39,433 --> 00:17:40,633
- Double whammy!
- Double!

406
00:17:41,167 --> 00:17:43,500
- Double whammy.
- I see the growth, Marla.

407
00:17:44,433 --> 00:17:45,600
Baby steps.

408
00:17:46,767 --> 00:17:48,500
[APRIL] You're all going off
on a tangent.

409
00:17:49,233 --> 00:17:50,267
Do whatever you want.

410
00:17:50,267 --> 00:17:51,233
I'm out.

411
00:17:52,067 --> 00:17:53,033
Huh?

412
00:17:53,433 --> 00:17:54,500
Huh?!

413
00:17:54,500 --> 00:17:56,633
First, she slept on us,
now she's walking out?

414
00:17:57,367 --> 00:17:58,367
Gosh!

415
00:17:58,367 --> 00:17:59,233
[MARLA'S PHONE CHIMES]

416
00:17:59,233 --> 00:18:00,467
She's got an attitude,
doesn't she?

417
00:18:00,467 --> 00:18:01,567
Totally.

418
00:18:01,767 --> 00:18:03,400
Cole: "Go to room 106
in 10 minutes."

419
00:18:03,400 --> 00:18:05,067
- [LIGHTS SWITCH OFF]
- [GIRLS GASPING]

420
00:18:05,633 --> 00:18:06,733
[ISOBEL] What the--

421
00:18:06,733 --> 00:18:07,700
[NYX] Again?

422
00:18:07,700 --> 00:18:09,400
- Ugh!
- [LIGHTS SWITCH OFF]

423
00:18:09,800 --> 00:18:10,800
[DOOR OPENS]

424
00:18:10,800 --> 00:18:12,533
[DOOR CREACKING]

425
00:18:13,767 --> 00:18:20,733
[UNSETTLING MUSIC BUILDS]

426
00:18:25,433 --> 00:18:27,400
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

427
00:18:27,400 --> 00:18:32,167
[DOOR CREAKS SHUT]

428
00:18:33,133 --> 00:18:34,100
[BAG THUDS]

429
00:18:36,767 --> 00:18:43,733
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

430
00:18:50,500 --> 00:18:51,567
Wait.

431
00:18:52,333 --> 00:18:54,600
Did you help Migo pass?

432
00:18:55,700 --> 00:18:57,600
[CHUCKLES WRYLY]
Why does it matter?

433
00:18:58,600 --> 00:19:01,200
[SMOOCHES]

434
00:19:02,533 --> 00:19:04,333
[EXHALES]

435
00:19:05,133 --> 00:19:09,133
So, you gave him a passing grade
even though he's been flunking?

436
00:19:10,800 --> 00:19:12,500
It's just grades.

437
00:19:13,767 --> 00:19:14,900
Come on, we don't--

438
00:19:14,900 --> 00:19:16,567
We don't have a lot of time.

439
00:19:16,567 --> 00:19:17,667
No!

440
00:19:18,800 --> 00:19:21,267
Did you know that Migo
leaked my photos?

441
00:19:23,133 --> 00:19:26,367
My whole life became a total
system crash because of him.

442
00:19:26,767 --> 00:19:28,900
How could you just
let him pass, sir?

443
00:19:28,933 --> 00:19:33,167
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

444
00:19:33,167 --> 00:19:34,667
You know what I've been through.

445
00:19:35,533 --> 00:19:36,733
I tell you everything.

446
00:19:37,800 --> 00:19:39,333
Migo has been harassing me.

447
00:19:39,733 --> 00:19:42,167
You know that Cole has
been treating me like shit.

448
00:19:42,767 --> 00:19:44,300
I've been telling you
everything.

449
00:19:44,767 --> 00:19:46,400
So, why did you let him pass?

450
00:19:46,400 --> 00:19:53,400
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

451
00:19:53,400 --> 00:19:54,867
[INHALES SHARPLY]

452
00:19:57,167 --> 00:19:58,367
Because...

453
00:20:00,467 --> 00:20:01,733
he knows about us.

454
00:20:02,467 --> 00:20:03,433
What?

455
00:20:04,600 --> 00:20:05,633
How?

456
00:20:05,633 --> 00:20:07,633
[MR. RAMIREZ] I don't know.

457
00:20:07,633 --> 00:20:09,300
But he has evidence.

458
00:20:09,733 --> 00:20:11,767
Enough to threaten me with,
that's for sure.

459
00:20:11,767 --> 00:20:13,533
He even wanted to go
to the school board.

460
00:20:14,467 --> 00:20:15,767
You know what would
happen to me

461
00:20:15,767 --> 00:20:16,867
if he did that?

462
00:20:18,633 --> 00:20:20,967
My teaching license
would get revoked.

463
00:20:20,967 --> 00:20:22,600
He won't do that.

464
00:20:22,600 --> 00:20:23,933
He's just all bark no bite.

465
00:20:23,933 --> 00:20:25,433
Migo's a coward.

466
00:20:25,433 --> 00:20:26,667
[SIGHS]

467
00:20:30,433 --> 00:20:31,633
Look.

468
00:20:32,633 --> 00:20:35,200
I only did it because
I wanted to protect you.

469
00:20:37,300 --> 00:20:39,400
Come on, I'm the only one
who cares about us.

470
00:20:40,300 --> 00:20:41,500
Do you really think...

471
00:20:41,500 --> 00:20:42,633
I'd let you get hurt?

472
00:20:43,400 --> 00:20:44,800
I'll talk to Migo.

473
00:20:44,800 --> 00:20:46,633
I'll troubleshoot this problem.

474
00:20:47,633 --> 00:20:48,767
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

475
00:20:49,767 --> 00:20:50,833
No. Don't.

476
00:20:51,533 --> 00:20:52,600
I've fixed it.

477
00:20:53,567 --> 00:20:54,667
Okay?

478
00:20:55,000 --> 00:20:57,700
He needs me to pass,
so I let him pass.

479
00:20:57,700 --> 00:20:59,200
So that he'll leave us alone.

480
00:20:59,500 --> 00:21:00,633
Just...

481
00:21:01,967 --> 00:21:03,300
just ignore the guy.

482
00:21:03,833 --> 00:21:04,867
No.

483
00:21:05,500 --> 00:21:06,467
[SIGHS]

484
00:21:06,467 --> 00:21:09,467
I won't let Migo bully me
ever again, okay?

485
00:21:10,800 --> 00:21:12,500
If we let him get away
with this,

486
00:21:12,500 --> 00:21:14,400
then he'll just keep
blackmailing us.

487
00:21:15,367 --> 00:21:17,667
Migo is malware,
and I have to remove him.

488
00:21:17,667 --> 00:21:18,833
You think this is a game?

489
00:21:19,767 --> 00:21:21,267
- No.
- No, right?

490
00:21:21,267 --> 00:21:22,733
No, it's not a game.

491
00:21:23,600 --> 00:21:26,400
But for some reason, your age
is really showing here, April.

492
00:21:27,433 --> 00:21:29,600
My job is on the line here.

493
00:21:30,400 --> 00:21:32,600
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

494
00:21:32,600 --> 00:21:33,567
I know, that's why...

495
00:21:33,567 --> 00:21:35,700
- I'm trying to...
- No. No, no... nope.

496
00:21:36,433 --> 00:21:37,700
No, you don't know.

497
00:21:39,433 --> 00:21:43,333
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

498
00:21:43,667 --> 00:21:45,867
Look, Migo and I
already talked about this.

499
00:21:46,933 --> 00:21:48,033
He needs me...

500
00:21:48,733 --> 00:21:49,867
to pass.

501
00:21:50,433 --> 00:21:52,467
It's a mutually
beneficial arrangement.

502
00:21:52,467 --> 00:21:53,467
So, just...

503
00:21:54,033 --> 00:21:55,467
leave the guy alone.

504
00:21:55,967 --> 00:21:57,033
Unless...

505
00:21:58,367 --> 00:22:00,900
you want me
to leave you alone.

506
00:22:03,033 --> 00:22:04,333
What?

507
00:22:05,433 --> 00:22:07,267
You want me to end this?

508
00:22:07,700 --> 00:22:11,033
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

509
00:22:11,033 --> 00:22:12,867
[EXHALES DEEPLY] Okay.

510
00:22:12,867 --> 00:22:13,867
Okay.

511
00:22:15,800 --> 00:22:16,833
You're right.

512
00:22:17,400 --> 00:22:18,500
I'm sorry.

513
00:22:19,033 --> 00:22:20,500
Okay.

514
00:22:22,000 --> 00:22:24,300
You're the only person
who understands me, April.

515
00:22:26,900 --> 00:22:29,067
I wouldn't know
what I'd do if I lost you.

516
00:22:29,533 --> 00:22:30,633
No.

517
00:22:31,767 --> 00:22:33,467
I can't lose you, Sir.

518
00:22:34,633 --> 00:22:35,767
So...

519
00:22:36,600 --> 00:22:37,767
promise me...

520
00:22:37,767 --> 00:22:39,033
you'll leave him alone?

521
00:22:39,967 --> 00:22:41,300
I promise.

522
00:22:42,700 --> 00:22:43,767
Promise?

523
00:22:46,533 --> 00:22:47,933
So let me do my job.

524
00:22:50,567 --> 00:22:51,833
[SMOOCHES] Good girl.

